. do nma/qa/crossval_nma_vs_r.do 

. * crossval_nma_vs_r.do — Cross-validation: Stata nma vs R netmeta
. *
. * Runs Stata nma on two published NMA datasets and compares treatment
. * effect estimates against R netmeta 3.3-1 benchmarks.
. *
. * Datasets:
. *   1. Senn et al. (2013) — Glucose-lowering drugs, 26 studies, 10 treatments
. *      Continuous outcome (HbA1c MD), pre-computed contrasts
. *   2. Dogliotti et al. (2014) — Anticoagulants in AF, 20 studies, 8 treatmen
> ts
. *      Binary outcome (stroke events), arm-level data
. *
. * R netmeta benchmarks generated using:
. *   library(netmeta); netmeta(TE, seTE, treat1, treat2, studlab, ...)
. *   REML random-effects, reference = Placebo
. *
. * Note on tau2 differences:
. *   R netmeta uses the graph-theoretical REML approach (Rucker 2012).
. *   Stata nma uses multivariate REML. This produces different tau2 values
. *   but treatment effect estimates converge (all within 0.04 except
. *   Benfluorex at 0.096, which has only 2 studies and is sensitive to tau2).
. *
. * Produces: crossval_nma_vs_r.xlsx with comparison tables for both datasets
. *
. * Run: stata-mp -b do crossval_nma_vs_r.do
. 
. version 16.0

. set more off

. set varabbrev off

. clear all

. 
. * --- Paths ---
. local pkg_dir "/home/tpcopeland/Stata-Tools/nma"

. local qa_dir "`pkg_dir'/qa"

. local outfile "`qa_dir'/crossval_nma_vs_r.xlsx"

. 
. * --- Setup adopath ---
. capture ado uninstall nma

. adopath ++ "`pkg_dir'"
